{"title":"Not April Fools’: Square Taper is back with Paul Comp 100% Pure Cranks!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/square-taper-paul-comp-100-pure-cranks/","date":1743519600000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-hero.webp\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" alt=\"(Photo / Paul Components)\" /></p>\n<p>Machinists extraordinaire, Paul Components Engineering, have reached into the way-back machine and decided to bring back the <a href=\"https://www.paulcomp.com/shop/components/drivetrain/cranksets/100-pure-paul-cranks/\">100% Pure Cranks</a>. This time around, the cranks will feature an updated design with a 3-bolt direct-mount chainring spline and self-extracting crankbolts.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-first-pic.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-first-pic.webp\" alt=\"Paul Components 100 Pure Crank first pic\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-first-pic.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-first-pic-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-first-pic-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-first-pic-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-first-pic-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-first-pic-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo / Paul Components)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Paul Comp Krëw says that it was Paul’s idea to bring these beauties back, but told the gang that he wanted to bring them back with a square taper. They were cautiously optimistic. That’s the benefit of having your name on the building: you get to do what you want.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-dialed.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-dialed.webp\" alt=\"Paul Components 100 Pure Crank dialed\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-dialed.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-dialed-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-dialed-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-dialed-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-dialed-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-dialed-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-top-view.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-top-view.webp\" alt=\"Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-top-view\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-top-view.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-top-view-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-top-view-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-top-view-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-top-view-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-top-view-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The team started testing the prototypes and were surprised to find that they could really hone in the q-factor and chainstay clearance of their steeds. It was just as simple as swapping in the right bottom bracket spindle length, just like the good ‘ol days.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-make-it-your-own.webp\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-make-it-your-own.webp\" alt=\"Paul Components 100 Pure Crank make it your own\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-make-it-your-own.webp 1024w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-make-it-your-own-240x300.webp 240w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-make-it-your-own-96x120.webp 96w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-make-it-your-own-768x960.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>They were able to get the chainring close to the chainstay to get the right chainline in the bigger rear cog using chainring offset (0, -3, and -6).   </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-silver.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-silver.webp\" alt=\"Paul Components 100 Pure Crank silver\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-silver.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-silver-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-silver-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-silver-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Silver</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-purple.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-purple.webp\" alt=\"Paul Components 100 Pure Crank purple\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-purple.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-purple-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-purple-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-purple-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Purple (obvi)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-black.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-black.webp\" alt=\"Paul Components 100 Pure Crank black\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-black.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-black-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-black-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-black-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Black</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter.webp\" alt=\"Paul Components 100 Pure Crank pewter\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Pewter</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The crank arms are CNC machined in Chico, California, using 2024 American alloy. This allows for “the removal of a lot of material for an elegant design”, while retaining optimal strength and stiffness. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>These beauts are available now. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>100% Pure Cranks Retail &amp; Detail</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter-arm.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter-arm.webp\" alt=\"Paul Components 100 Pure Crank pewter arm\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter-arm.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter-arm-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter-arm-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter-arm-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter-arm-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-pewter-arm-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-snacks.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-snacks.webp\" alt=\"Paul Components 100 Pure Crank snacks\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-snacks.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-snacks-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-snacks-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-snacks-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-snacks-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Paul-Components-100-Pure-Crank-snacks-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $308</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Material: American Milled 2024 Aluminum</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Lengths: 155, 160, 165, 170, 175, 180</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Weight: 516g (Pair of 180mm) including chainring bolts, crankbolts, and extractor caps</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Anodized Colors: Black, Purple, Silver, or Pewter</li>\n\n\n\n<li>J.I.S. Square Taper</li>\n\n\n\n<li>3-Bolt SRAM Direct Mount Spline</li>\n\n\n\n<li>CNC Machined by us in sunny Chico, California</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Price: $308</li>\n\n\n\n<li>In stock: NOW</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.paulcomp.com/\" target=\"_blank\">PaulComp.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/square-taper-paul-comp-100-pure-cranks/\">Not April Fools’: Square Taper is back with Paul Comp 100% Pure Cranks!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b88a79aaf29999ff743f2af142b0b93a4c3cced5cfa05abe5953e7ea7bbc5cd2","category":"Cycling"}